  "time_ut": 1661925534,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Problem due to coins",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The businessmen who are doing small scale business activities in Hatton city say that they have become very uncomfortable due to the fact that wholesalers in Hatton area and some foodstuff distribution institutions do not provide goods for retail coins.",
        "Small-scale businessmen who sell school equipment and food items for school children near the main schools in Hatton town have become helpless.",
        "The students studying in the school come to their shop and give them rupees, two rupees and five rupees coins and buy the food and school equipment they need. Vendors claim that companies that distribute food items and school supplies do not accept the retail coins.",
        "The traders claim that they are doing business targeting school children and sell goods for retail coins between 5000-10000 rupees per day, and even though they have a large amount of money collected in their possession, no one takes those retail coins to turn the money into notes.",
        "Regarding the non-receipt of retail coins, when we asked some wholesalers and food distributors in Hatton, they said that they do not receive retail coins because it takes a long time to count the retail coins."
      ],
